[http://www.forthfreak.net/misc/interpreters/PsiForth.asc PsiForth] has been written in OPL-32, the ROM-resident interpreter of Psion 5. It uses
a form of byte-token threading for primitives, and indirect threading for user-defined words.
You can't call machine code from [http://www.forthfreak.net/misc/interpreters/PsiForth.asc PsiForth] , additional primitives would have to be written in OPL, by adding to the source code of [http://www.forthfreak.net/misc/interpreters/PsiForth.asc PsiForth] .

http://www.forthfreak.net/misc/interpreters/PsiForth.asc
http://www.forthfreak.net/misc/interpreters/PsiForth.tgz

